This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance of training generalized linear models, which falls under the category of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses system-level performance bottlenecks and optimizations, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). The use of data partitioning and cache line prefetching could also be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper mentions the comparison of their results to state-of-the-art implementations, which could fall under cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
